{"parse":{"title":"city","pageid":4828,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|City}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|citie|cittie|cyte|cytee||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|en|enm|cite}}, {{der+|en|fro|citet|cite|nocap=1}}, {{der+|en|la-lat|civitas|cīvitātem|city|nocap=1}}, in {{der|en|la-cla|-}} \"citizenry\", derived from {{m|la|cīvis|t=fellow-citizen}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ḱey-|t=lie down; settle}}. Cognate with {{cog|ang|hīwan|g=p|t=members of one's household, servants}}. See {{m|en|hewe}}. {{doublet|en|civitas}}. Mostly displaced native {{ncog|ang|burg}}, whence {{w|Modern English}} {{m|en|borough}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|sĭt'''′'''ē}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈsɪti/}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈsɪtʰiː]|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈsɪtʰɪj]|[ˈsɪʔɪj]|a=SSB}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-uk-city.ogg|a=UK}}\n** {{IPA|en|/sɪtɪ/|a=Northern England,Conservative RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈsɪt.i/ [ˈsɪɾ.i]|a=US}}\n*** {{audio|en|en-us-city.ogg|a=US|IPA=[ˈsɪɾi]}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈsɪt.iː/ [ˈsiɾ.iː]|[ˈsɪɾ.iː]|a=AU}}\n*** {{audio|en|EN-AU ck1 city.ogg|a=AU}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈsɪʔe]|[ˈsɪtʰe]|[ˈsɪʔɪ]|[ˈsɪtʰɪ]|[ˈsɪʔi]|[ˈsɪtʰi]|a=Scotland}}\n* {{hyph|en|cit|y}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɪti|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n[[File:Empire State Building Aerial.JPG|thumb|Part of New York City, a large '''city''' with many tall buildings.]]\n[[File:Aerial view of Wells.jpg|thumb|Despite its small size, Wells is a '''city''' because of its cathedral.]]\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q515}}A large [[settlement]], bigger than a [[town]]; sometimes with a specific legal definition, depending on the place.\n#: {{ux|en|São Paulo is the largest '''city''' in South America.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 6-3|act=I|scene=i|page=147|column=2|passage=Ah, knovv you not the '''Citie''' fauours them, / And they haue troupes of Souldiers at their beck?}}\n#* {{RQ:Ferguson Zollenstein|IV|passage=So this was my future home, I thought!{{...}}Backed by towering hills, the but faintly discernible purple line of the French boundary off to the southwest, a sky of palest Gobelin flecked with fat, fleecy little clouds, it in truth looked a dear little '''city'''; the '''city''' of one's dreams.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-09-07|volume=408|issue=8852|magazine=w:The Economist\n|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/briefing/21585002-enthusiasts-think-data-services-can-change-cities-century-much-electricity The multiplexed metropolis]\n|passage=But clever '''cities''' will not necessarily be better ones.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2014-06-14|volume=411|issue=8891|magazine=w:The Economist\n|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/science-and-technology/21604091-it-possible-sniff-out-problems-sewer-pipes-they-happen-its-gas It's a gas]\n|passage=One of the hidden glories of Victorian engineering is proper drains. Isolating a '''city'''’s effluent and shipping it away in underground sewers has probably saved more lives than any medical procedure except vaccination.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2020-07-15|author=Mike Brown talks to Paul Clifton|title=Leading London's \"hidden heroes\"|journal=Rail|page=42|text=All our stations have changed. We have to constrain numbers. We have to mandate face coverings. These are massive changes in what is a public transport '''city'''. This is not a car '''city'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Ivana Kottasová|title=‘Kamikaze’ drones are the latest threat for Ukraine. Here’s what we know|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/10/17/europe/kamikaze-drones-explained-update-intl|date=2022-10-17|passage=The Ukrainian government says Kyiv, Vinnytsia, Odesa, Zaporizhzhia and other '''cities''' have suffered a barrage of drone attacks, and pleaded with Western countries to step up their assistance in the face of the new challenge. {{...}} But Ukraine claimed its forces had shot down one of these drones for the first time last month near the '''city''' of Kupyansk in Kharkiv.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK|historical|_|in|_|Ireland|and|Commonwealth}} A settlement granted special status by royal charter or [[letters patent]]; traditionally, a settlement with a [[cathedral]] regardless of size.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1976|author=Cornelius P. Darcy|title=The Encouragement of the Fine Arts in Lancashire, 1760-1860|publisher=Manchester University Press|isbn=9780719013300|page=20\n|passage=Manchester, incorporated in 1838, was made the centre of a bishopric in 1847 and became a '''city''' in 1853. Liverpool was transformed into a '''city''' by Royal Charter when the new diocese of Liverpool was created in 1880.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2014|author=Graham Rutt|title=Cycling Britain's Cathedrals Volume 1|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=9781326056049|page=307\n|passage=St Davids itself is the smallest '''city''' in Great Britain, with a population of less than 2,000.}}\n# {{lb|en|Australia}} The [[central business district]]; [[downtown]].\n#: {{ux|en|I'm going into the '''city''' today to do some shopping.}}\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A large amount of something {{q|used after the noun}}.\n#: {{ux|en|It’s video game '''city''' in here!}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{l|en|settlement}}\n\n====Hyponyms====\n{{col4|en\n|15-minute city\n|agrocity\n|agropolis\n|capital\n|capital city\n|closed city\n|cathedral city\n|city on a hill\n|city upon a hill\n|garden city\n|global city\n|Hanseatic city\n|host city\n|megacity\n|metropolis\n|metropolitan city\n|open city\n|prefecture-level city\n|province-level city\n|state-level city\n|sister city\n|twin city\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en\n|15-minute city\n|agrocity|city pigeon\n|alpha city\n|Angel City\n|Angeles City\n|anticity\n|beta city\n|capital city\n|caravan city\n|cardboard city\n|cathedral city\n|Cavite City\n|central city\n|Chocolate City\n|chocolate city\n|cidiot\n|citaye\n|citied\n|citification\n|citizen\n|city administrator\n|city and county\n|city banker\n|city block\n|citybound\n|city boy\n|city break\n|city-builder\n|city-building game\n|citybus\n|city bus\n|city center\n|city centre\n|citycen