i: {{t+check|gug|táva}}\n* Gujarati: {{t+|gu|શહેર}}, {{t+|gu|નગર}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t|ht|vil}}\n* Hausa: {{t+|ha|birni}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|kūlanakauhale}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|עִיר|f|tr=ir}}\n* Hiligaynon: {{t|hil|dakbanwa}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|शहर|m}}, {{t+|hi|नगर|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|város}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|xtat}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|borg|f}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|urbo}}, {{t+|io|civito}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|kota}}\n* Ingush: {{t|inh|пхье}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|citate}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|cathair|f}}, {{t|ga|baile mór|m}}\n* Istriot: {{t|ist|sità|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|città|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|都市|tr=とし, toshi}}, {{t+|ja|都会|tr=とかい, tokai}}, {{t+|ja|町|tr=まち, machi}} (e.g. 町で - \"in the city\"), {{t+|ja|市|tr=し, shi}} {{qualifier|compound}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|ꦏꦸꦛ|tr=kutha}}{{qualifier|ngoko}}, {{t+|jv|ꦏꦶꦛ|tr=kitha}}{{qualifier|krama}}\n* Kaitag: {{t|xdq|шагьар}}\n* Kalmyk: {{t|xal|балһсн}}\n* Kannada: {{t+|kn|ನಗರ}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|lakanbalen}}\n* Karachay-Balkar: {{t|krc|шахар}}\n* Karelian: {{t|krl|linna}}\n* Kashubian: {{t|csb|miasto|n}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|қала}}, {{t|kk|шаһар}} {{qualifier|literary}}\n* Khakas: {{t|kjh|саар}}, {{t|kjh|тура}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|ទីក្រុង}}, {{t+|km|បុរី}}, {{t+|km|នគរ}}\n* Komi:\n*: Komi-Permyak: {{t|koi|кар}}\n*: Komi-Zyrian: {{t|kpv|кар}}\n* Konkani: {{t|kok|xar}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|도시(都市)}}, {{t+|ko|시내(市內)}}, {{t+|ko|시(市)}} {{qualifier|compound}}\n* Kumyk: {{t|kum|шагьар}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t+|ckb|شار}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|bajar|m}}, {{t+|kmr|şar|m}}\n* Kusunda: {{t|kgg|səhər}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|шаар}}, {{t+|ky|калаа}}, {{t+|ky|кен}}\n* Ladin: {{t|lld|zità|f}}\n* Lak: {{t-check|lbe|шагьру}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ຊຽງ}}, {{t|lo|ທານີ}}, {{t+|lo|ເມືອງ}}, {{t|lo|ນະຄອນ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|urbs|f}}, {{t+|la|civitas|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|pilsēta|f}} (or {{t|lv|lielpilsēta|f}} if the distinction between ''city'' and ''town'' is important)\n* Leonese: {{t|roa-leo|ciudá|f}}\n* Lezgi: {{t|lez|