ech==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|cs|noun form}}\n\n# {{infl of|cs|cit||nom//acc//voc//ins|p}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|fi|en|city}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-p|siti|h=ci.ty}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|fi|Q738570}} {{syn of|fi|liikekeskusta||central business district}} {{gl|central area of a city}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{fi-decl-valo|cit|||y|ä}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fi\n|citykani\n|citykarhu\n|citykulttuuri\n|citymaasturi\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2026-05-14}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|it|en|city}}. {{doublet|it|città}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|sìty<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|f|#}}\n\n# {{l|en|city}} (financial district of a city)\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|it|city bike}}\n* {{l|it|city car}}\n* {{l|it|city manager}}\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|cite}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|sv|en|city}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-city.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|n}}\n\n# [[inner city]], the commercial [[centre]] of a medium-sized or larger city\n#: {{ux|sv|Lite närmare '''city''', i närheten av konstmuseet, ligger Norrköpings mest attraktiva lägenheter|A little closer to '''the town centre''', next to the art museum, you'll find Norrköping's most attractive apartments}}\n#: {{ux|sv|Det finns mycket att förbättra i vårt '''city'''|There are many things that need improvement in our '''inner city'''}}\n#* {{quote-song|sv|year=1991|author=w:Bobby Ljunggren; w:sv:Håkan Almqvist; Eva Lindblad|artist=[[w:Angel (Swedish band)|Angel]]|title=[[w:Sommaren i city|Sommaren i '''city''']]|trans-title=[The] summer in the '''city'''|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sPZPiZWqfwE|text=Sommaren i '''city''' 1990 – kommer du ihåg mig? Minns du vad som hände? Minns du vad du sa när du träffade mig? Kommer du ihåg mig – 1990, sommaren i '''city'''? Minns du var vi var? Och minns du vad vi sa?|t=[The] summer in the '''city''' [\"Sommar i city\" would literally be \"summer in the city,\" but \"the summer in the city\" sounds a bit unidiomatic], 1990 [\"in 1990\" – Swedish skips the \"in\"] – do you remember me? Do you remember what happened? Do you remember what you said when you met me? Do you remember me – 1990, [the] summer in the '''city'''? Do you remember where we were? And do you remember what we said?}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* {{m|sv|centrum}} is used for the commercial centre of suburbs and small or medium-sized towns.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|sv|centrum}}\n* {{l|sv|innerstad}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}"}}